instructions:
Ingredients:
• 2 Apples, peeled, cored, and cut into small chunks
• 2 Oranges, peeled and segmented
• 10 Small potatoes, peeled and diced
• 2 tablespoons olive oil
• ¼ teaspoon ground nutmeg
• ¼ teaspoon paprika
• 2 tablespoons chopped fresh parsley leaves
• Salt and pepper, to taste
• 2 eggs

Directions:
1. Heat the olive oil in a large non-stick skillet over medium-high heat.
2. Add the diced potatoes to the pan and season with the nutmeg, paprika, and some salt and pepper.
3. Sauté the potatoes until golden brown and tender, about 8-10 minutes.
4. Add the apples and oranges and sauté for 3-4 minutes, until apples are tender.
5. In a small bowl, whisk together the eggs.
6. Pour the eggs over the potatoes, apple, and orange and scramble together until ingredients are well incorporated and eggs are cooked, about 2-3 minutes.
7. Finish with a sprinkle of the chopped parsley leaves.
8. Serve warm and enjoy your Apple Orange Potato Scramble!
title: Apple Orange Potato Scramble

instructions:
Ingredients:
2 oranges, peeled and cut into wedges
3 small potatoes, peeled and cut into cubes
3 ripe peaches, peeled and cubed
1/2 cup cooked rice

Directions:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.
2. Toss potatoes in a bowl with some olive oil, salt, and pepper. Spread potatoes onto a baking sheet and bake for 25-30 minutes, or until potatoes are golden and crispy.
3. Peel and cube oranges and peaches and place in a medium bowl.
4. Once potatoes are ready, add to the bowl with the oranges and peaches.
5. Pour cooked rice into the bowl and mix ingredients together until evenly distributed.
6. Serve the Orange Potato Peach Rice Bowl warm!
title: Orange Potato Peach Rice Bowl
